An heirloom tomato is an open-pollinated (non-hybrid) heirloom cultivar of tomato, that can be classified into four categories: family heirlooms, commercial heirlooms, mystery heirlooms, and created heirlooms. They usually have a shorter shelf life and less disease resistance than hybrids bred to resist against specific diseases.
